00:07:57.310 --> 00:08:05.910
Let us do another problem which I wanted to
do. I will not be giving you any method, I

00:08:05.910 --> 00:08:12.699
just want to do an example problem since that
example will be enough to understand the topic.

00:08:12.699 --> 00:08:14.770
The question says we have been given two lines:

00:08:14.770 --> 00:08:23.590
(x-1)/1 = (y-2)/2 = (z-3)/3, L1 is this

00:08:23.590 --> 00:08:40.729
L2 has been given as (x-2)/4 = (y-3)/5 = (z-1)/6.

00:08:40.729 --> 00:08:56.990
The

00:08:56.990 --> 00:09:09.630
question says find the line
perpendicular to L1 and L2 and passing through

00:09:09.630 --> 00:09:21.350
1,1,1. How to solve this problem?

00:09:21.350 --> 00:09:26.410
So you have been given line L1. Let me write
answer here:

00:09:26.410 --> 00:09:33.839
Let us say this is L1 and this is L2. You
have been given a1_vector, b1_vector, a2_vector,

00:09:33.839 --> 00:09:42.720
b2_vector. You have been asked to find line
3 for which you know that it is perpendicular

00:09:42.720 --> 00:09:44.930
to both, and it passes through the point.

00:09:44.930 --> 00:09:48.830
To find the equation of line, you need a point,
which you already have, and you need a parallel

00:09:48.830 --> 00:09:53.990
vector. What is speciality of parallel vector?
That the line is perpendicular to line L1

00:09:53.990 --> 00:10:02.310
and L2. Hence, the parallel vector will be
perpendicular to both b1 and b2.

00:10:02.310 --> 00:10:06.519
And as soon as I say this, it should flash
into your mind, that this is basically asking

00:10:06.519 --> 00:10:10.560
you to take a cross product. Thats it.

00:10:10.560 --> 00:10:15.810
If you cannot recall this, please become more
thorough with understanding the physical meaning

00:10:15.810 --> 00:10:20.600
of dot product and cross product. We have
discussed here dot product: perpendicularity

00:10:20.600 --> 00:10:23.820
condition of dot product already. We have
done in the last video, that dot product is

00:10:23.820 --> 00:10:31.519
used for finding angles. So as soon as I say,
it should come to your mind, the vector perpendicular

00:10:31.519 --> 00:10:35.220
to two vectors is the cross product of two
vectors.

00:10:35.220 --> 00:10:42.320
So what you have to do is that you have to
find b3_vector = b1 \cross b2, and if you

00:10:42.320 --> 00:10:51.640
do, you should remember that for cross product
you have to do this i, j, k â€” and opening

00:10:51.640 --> 00:10:52.730
up the determinant.

00:10:52.730 --> 00:11:06.890
So if you do that, this will be: i(-3) + j(6)
+ k(-3). Is this perpendicular to b1 and b2?

00:11:06.890 --> 00:11:14.770
You should remember that condition of perpendicularity
is dot product is zero.

00:11:14.770 --> 00:11:21.800
So if you take -3 + 12 - 9, that is dotted
with b1, it comes out to be 0.

00:11:21.800 --> 00:11:27.029
If you dot with b2, -12 + 30 -18, so 30 - 30
= 0. So it is perpendicular to both b1 and

00:11:27.029 --> 00:11:28.029
b2.

00:11:28.029 --> 00:11:29.700
And you already have point.

00:11:29.700 --> 00:11:44.529
So the equation of line L3 could be easily
written as: (x-1)/3 = (y-1)/6 = (z-1)/(-3).

00:11:44.529 --> 00:11:52.029
This line is perpendicular to both the lines
and passes through (1,1,1).

00:11:52.029 --> 00:11:56.630
I hope that you are able to understand this,
understand how important the understanding

00:11:56.630 --> 00:12:02.220
of vectors is, and how to solve the problems.
We discussed two things here: how to find

00:12:02.220 --> 00:12:07.910
the perpendicular distance of a point from
a line. For that, we can remember this formula

00:12:07.910 --> 00:12:15.220
of \lambda. Calculate \lambda, calculate the
point, and when you get the coordinates of

00:12:15.220 --> 00:12:19.670
the point, you subtract from the original
point to get the distance. I have given you

00:12:19.670 --> 00:12:22.390
a homework problem, so please do that at home.

00:12:22.390 --> 00:12:27.380
And then we did a problem of finding a line
perpendicular to two lines. For that you are

00:12:27.380 --> 00:12:31.580
taking the cross product of the parallel vectors,
and then you will get the equation of the

00:12:31.580 --> 00:12:32.580
line.

